Class StandardLogFilter

java.lang.Object
com.dua3.utility.logging.StandardLogFilter
All Implemented Interfaces:
LogFilter
public class StandardLogFilter extends Object implements LogFilter
The LogFilter class is an implementation of the LogEntryFilter interface that filters log entries based on their name and log levels defined on package/class levels.

      public StandardLogFilter(String name)
      Constructs a LogFilter instance with the specified name. The initial global log level is set to LogLevel.INFO. A level map is also initialized with the global log level.
      Parameters:
      name - the name of the log filter

    • test

      public boolean test(Instant instant, String loggerName, LogLevel lvl, String mrk, Supplier<String> msg, String location, @Nullable Throwable t)
      Description copied from interface: LogFilter
      Tests if a log entry, specified by its components, should be processed.
      Specified by:
      test in interface LogFilter
      Parameters:
      instant - the timestamp of the log entry
      loggerName - the name of the logger that generated the log entry
      lvl - the log level of the log entry
      mrk - the marker associated with the log entry, can be null
      msg - the message of the log entry
      location - the location where the log entry was generated, typically a code context such as a class or method name
      t - the throwable associated with the log entry, can be null
      Returns:
      true, if the log entry should be processed, false if it should be filtered out
